City of Cannelton v. Denny. City of Cannelton v. Huber. [No. 21,271. [No. 21,272.

Filed April 23, 1909.]

Filed April 27, 1909.] From Ferry Circuit Court; Christopher W. Cook, Judge. Prosecutions by the City of Cannelton against Oscar Denny and Emil I-Iuber. From judgments for defendants, plaintiff appeals. Affirmed. William M. Waldschmidt, for appellant. Philip Zoercher, for appellees. Montgomery, J.

The questions presented by the record in these cases are in all respects the same as those decided in City of Cannelton v. Collins (1909), ante, 193, and upon the authority of that case the judgments are affirmed.
